        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>Sicilian (ancient pottery style) [300020179], South Italian (Greek pottery style) [300020172], Greek pottery styles [300020113], Aegean pottery styles [300020105], Aegean styles [300106921], Aegean [300020059], Mediterranean (Early Western World) [300020058], Early Western World [300019255], styles, periods, and cultures by region [300111079], Styles and Periods (hierarchy name) [300015646], Styles and Periods Facet [300264088]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Hellenistic pottery style known from a site at Centuripe, Sicily. It is characterized by the use of a combination of relief decoration and painted scenes, which are distinctive in depicting figures painted in various colors, imitating mural paintings.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079228/Grove Art Online (2008-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Se refiere a un estilo de cerámica Helenística conocido a partir de un sitio en Centuripe, Sicilia. Se caracteriza por el uso de una combinación de decoración en relieve y escenas pintadas que son distintivas en la representación de figuras pintadas en varios colores, imitando murales.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Verwijst naar de Hellenistische aardewerkstijl die bekend is van de opgravingen in Centuripe op Sicilië. De stijl kenmerkt zich door een gecombineerd gebruik van reliëfdecoratie en geschilderde afbeeldingen, waarin de figuren zijn geschilderd in verschillende kleuren en die lijken op muurschilderingen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052611/Lunsingh Scheurleer, Griekse ceramiek (1936)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>指稱於西元前四世紀至西元前一世紀間發展的一種希臘陶器風格，以位於西西里島的辰士力帕(Centuripe)遺址聞名。此風格的特徵為結合浮雕式裝飾與彩繪場景合，其場景特色是以各種顏色描繪人體，模擬壁畫中的繪畫。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
